{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:job.28",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 28,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 28",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 28 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.28.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:1",
      "text": "“Surely there is a mine for silver, and a place for gold which they refine.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.28.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:2",
      "text": "Iron is taken out of the earth, and copper is smelted from the ore.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.28.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:3",
      "text": "Men put an end to darkness, and search out to the farthest bound the ore in gloom and deep darkness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.28.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:4",
      "text": "They open shafts in a valley away from where men live; they are forgotten by travelers, they hang afar from men, they swing to and fro.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.28.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:5",
      "text": "As for the earth, out of it comes bread; but underneath it is turned up as by fire.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.28.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:6",
      "text": "Its stones are the place of sapphires, and it has dust of gold.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.28.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:7",
      "text": "“That path no bird of prey knows, and the falcon's eye has not seen it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.28.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:8",
      "text": "The proud beasts have not trodden it; the lion has not passed over it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.28.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:9",
      "text": "“Man puts his hand to the flinty rock, and overturns mountains by the roots.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.28.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:10",
      "text": "He cuts out channels in the rocks, and his eye sees every precious thing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.28.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:11",
      "text": "He binds up the streams so that they do not trickle, and the thing that is hid he brings forth to light.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.28.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:12",
      "text": "“But where shall wisdom be found? And where is the place of understanding?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.28.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:13",
      "text": "Man does not know the way to it, and it is not found in the land of the living.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.28.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:14",
      "text": "The deep says, ‘It is not in me,’ and the sea says, ‘It is not with me.’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.28.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:15",
      "text": "It cannot be gotten for gold, and silver cannot be weighed as its price.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.28.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:16",
      "text": "It cannot be valued in the gold of Ophir, in precious onyx or sapphire.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.28.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:17",
      "text": "Gold and glass cannot equal it, nor can it be exchanged for jewels of fine gold.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.28.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:18",
      "text": "No mention shall be made of coral or of crystal; the price of wisdom is above pearls.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.28.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:19",
      "text": "The topaz of Ethiopia cannot compare with it, nor can it be valued in pure gold.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.28.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:20",
      "text": "“Whence then comes wisdom? And where is the place of understanding?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.28.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:21",
      "text": "It is hid from the eyes of all living, and concealed from the birds of the air.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.28.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:22",
      "text": "Abaddon and Death say, ‘We have heard a rumor of it with our ears.’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.28.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:23",
      "text": "“God understands the way to it, and he knows its place.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.28.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:24",
      "text": "For he looks to the ends of the earth, and sees everything under the heavens.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.28.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:25",
      "text": "When he gave to the wind its weight, and meted out the waters by measure;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.28.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:26",
      "text": "when he made a decree for the rain, and a way for the lightning of the thunder;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.28.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:27",
      "text": "then he saw it and declared it; he established it, and searched it out.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.28.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:28",
      "text": "And he said to man, ‘Behold, the fear of the Lord, that is wisdom; and to depart from evil is understanding.’ ”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
